column5: Pulled the boat out and went over it bow to stern and the trailer, tires needed a bit of air. Hooked up the lights and everything lit up just like it should. Fired up the motor and it started just like it has every time since I bought it from Rizzo about this time 4 years ago. Getting it wet next week hopefully, maybe even slimed.

Well good luck when you do get out!  I'm still weeks away from a boat trip.  May try and convince the kids to hit the local legal side of the river in town tomorrow for some crappie.  But no they want chicken for dinner...
